apig insert directly into dynanodb with service proxy. 
dont need lambda

1) create dynamodb table with partition key. LESSON: always look at the POST Request examples 
Can create table with AttributeName and KeyType. keytype = Hash|Range. hash=partition key, range = sort key

The docs are wrong saying you need an AttributeName. You need the AttributeDefinitions. 

An AttributeDefinition ISNT the string:string for tableName:"mytable". 
Attribute Deifnitions are type defintions to allocate memory space. 


{
    "AttributeDefinitions": [
        {
            "AttributeName": "ForumName",
            "AttributeType": "S"
        },
        {
            "AttributeName": "Subject",
            "AttributeType": "S"
        },
        {
            "AttributeName": "Date",
            "AttributeType": "S"
        }
    ],
    "TableName": "myTable",
    "KeySchema": [
        {
            "AttributeName": "ForumName",
            "KeyType": "HASH"
        },
        {
            "AttributeName": "Subject",
            "KeyType": "RANGE"
        }
    ],
    "LocalSecondaryIndexes": [
        {
            "IndexName": "SecondIndex",
            "KeySchema": [
                {
                    "AttributeName": "ForumName",
                    "KeyType": "HASH"
                },
                {
                    "AttributeName": "Date",
                    "KeyType": "RANGE"
                }
            ],
            "Projection": {
                "ProjectionType": "KEYS_ONLY"
            }
        }
    ],
    "ProvisionedThroughput": {
        "ReadCapacityUnits": 1,
        "WriteCapacityUnits": 1
    },
    "Tags": [ 
      { 
         "Key": "AWSCLI",
         "Value": "AWSCLI"
      }
   ]
}




